<section xml:id="csp-name-turtles_mixed-up-code-practice">
  <title>Mixed Up Code Practice</title>
  <p>Try to solve each of the following. Click the <em>Check</em> button to check each solution. You will be told if
    your solution is too short, has a block in the wrong order, or you are using the wrong block. Some of the problems
    have an extra block that isn&#8217;t needed in the correct solution.</p>
  <exercise label="cspnameturtles_mixedupturtles1" numbered="yes" adaptive="yes" indentation="hide" language="python">
    <statement>
      <p>The following program segment should draw a red line. The blocks have been mixed up. Drag the blocks from the
        left and put them in the correct order on the right. Click the <em>Check Me</em> button to check your solution.</p>
    </statement>
    <blocks>
      <block order="4">
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>from turtle import *</cline>
          <cline>space = Screen()</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>from turtle import *</cline>
          <cline>space = screen() </cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
      <block order="2">
        <cline>ani = Turtle()</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="1">
        <cline>ani.color("red")</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="3" correct="no">
        <cline>ani.color(red) </cline>
      </block>
      <block order="6">
        <cline>ani.forward(100)</cline>
      </block>
    </blocks>
  </exercise>
  <exercise label="cspnameturtles_mixedupturtles2" numbered="yes" adaptive="yes" indentation="hide" language="python">
    <statement>
      <p>The following program segment should draw an equilateral triangle. The blocks have been mixed up. Drag the
        blocks from the left and put them in the correct order on the right. Click the <em>Check Me</em> button to check
        your solution.</p>
    </statement>
    <blocks>
      <block order="1">
        <cline>from turtle import *</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="4" correct="no">
        <cline>from Turtle import * </cline>
      </block>
      <block order="3">
        <cline>space = Screen()</cline>
        <cline>mik = Turtle()</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="2">
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>mik.left(120)</cline>
          <cline>mik.forward(100)</cline>
          <cline>mik.left(120)</cline>
          <cline>mik.forward(100)</cline>
          <cline>mik.left(120)</cline>
          <cline>mik.forward(100)</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>mik.left(60)</cline>
          <cline>mik.forward(100)</cline>
          <cline>mik.left(60)</cline>
          <cline>mik.forward(100)</cline>
          <cline>mik.left(60)</cline>
          <cline>mik.forward(100) </cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
    </blocks>
  </exercise>
  <exercise label="cspnameturtles_mixedupturtles3" numbered="yes" adaptive="yes" indentation="hide" language="python">
    <statement>
      <p>The following program segment should create two turtles, Ari and Chris. Ari should have a pensize of 20 and
        draw a line to the west, while Chris will have the standard pensize and draw a line to the east. The blocks have
        been mixed up. Drag the blocks from the left and put them in the correct order on the right. Click the <em>Check
        Me</em> button to check your solution.</p>
      <p>Note that we could do the ari commands either before or after the chris commands. Assume we want to move ari
        first.</p>
    </statement>
    <blocks>
      <block order="3">
        <cline>from turtle import *</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="1">
        <cline>space = Screen()</cline>
        <cline>ari = Turtle()</cline>
        <cline>chris = Turtle()</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="2">
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>ari.pensize(20)</cline>
          <cline>ari.left(180)</cline>
          <cline>ari.forward(100)</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>ari.pensize(20)</cline>
          <cline>ari.forward(100) </cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
      <block order="5">
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>chris.forward(100)</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>chris.left(90)</cline>
          <cline>chris.forward(100) </cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
    </blocks>
  </exercise>
  <exercise label="cspnameturtles_mixedupturtles4" numbered="yes" adaptive="yes" indentation="hide" language="python">
    <statement>
      <p>The following program segment should draw a red line, starting from the postion (10, 30). The blocks have been
        mixed up. Drag the blocks from the left and put them in the correct order on the right. Click the <em>Check Me</em>
        button to check your solution.</p>
    </statement>
    <blocks>
      <block order="2">
        <cline>from turtle import *</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="8">
        <cline>space = Screen()</cline>
        <cline>nic = Turtle()</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="1">
        <cline>nic.color("red")</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="5">
        <cline>nic.penup()</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="7">
        <choice correct="yes">
          <cline>nic.goto(10,30)</cline>
        </choice>
        <choice>
          <cline>nic.goto("10,30") </cline>
        </choice>
      </block>
      <block order="4">
        <cline>nic.pendown()</cline>
      </block>
      <block order="3">
        <cline>nic.forward(100)</cline>
      </block>
    </blocks>
  </exercise>
  <exercise label="cspnameturtles_mixedupturtles5" numbered="yes" adaptive="yes" indentation="hide" language="python">
